<div id="about">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="small-8 small-centered medium-uncentered medium-4 columns about">
			<%= image_tag('profile_picture.png', id: "profile_picture", alt: 'Ryan O\'Connor') %>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<div class="medium-pull-3 columns">
				<h2 id="about_header" class="about text-center">About Me</h2>
			</div>

			<p class="about_text">
				I'm Ryan O'Connor and I am currently in my 3rd year of software engineering at the University of Ottawa. During my spare time I like to work on coding projects and or learn about the latest and greatest in computer technology.
			</p>
			<p class="about_text">
				Currently I'm VP Academic at the <%= link_to "Software Engineering Student Association", "http://uottawa-sesa.ca" %> where I help organize weekly Ruby on Rails tutorials, study sessions, and monthly coding events for students.
			</p>
			<p class="about_text"> 
				When I'm taking a break from coding, I like to go skating, snowmobiling, or enjoying my time out on the water.    
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="education">
	<div class="subtitle">
		<div class="row">
			<h2 class="text-center">Education</h2>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">University of Ottawa</h3>
			<p class="date">September 2012 - Current</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>BASc in Software Engineering</strong>
			<p>
				My studies at the University of Ottawa have allowed me to develop strong design skills by using requirements engineering techniques, analysis level diagrams, and design level diagrams. I've also learned how to translate requirements and diagrams into quality software. Java has been used as the main programming language for learning, however I've also had the opportunity to use HTML, CSS, SQL, and Ruby.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row paragraph">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">Charlottenburg D.H.S.</h3>
			<p class="date">September 2009 - June 2012</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>French Immersion Certificate</strong>
			<p>
				I graduated from a small high school of about 300 people, where I earned my bilingualism certificate. In 11th grade, I decided to take a programming course where we learned the beginnings of Visual Basic. I loved programming so much that I decided to continue with programming taking a 12th grade Java programming course which was the deciding factor in pursuing Software Engineering as a post secondary study.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="experience">
	<div class="subtitle">
		<div class="row">
			<h2 class="text-center">Experience</h2>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">Bell Canada</h3>
			<p class="date">June 2014 - August 2014</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>VoIP Manager - Service Assurance and Development</strong>
			<p>
				At Bell Canada I provided quality assurance for Bell's VoIP platform. I aided customers with validation testing and verified that their results were as expected by analyzing SIP traces using Wireshark. I was also part of testing for new version releases and aided with diagnosing system failures. During my time working at Bell Canada I implemented a call forwarding feature on FreeSwitch for internal release testing.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row paragraph">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">SigmaPoint Technologies</h3>
			<p class="date">May 2013 - August 2013</p>
		</div>

		<div class="small-12 medium-8 columns">
			<strong>Kontron Mechanic</strong>
			<p>
				SigmaPoint Technologies is an electronics manufacturer, where I worked as a Kontron mechanic. I assembled, diagnosed, and repaired CompactPCI boards and server boards. I worked under the Toyota Production System, used by SigmaPoint to provide quality products in a fast and efficient manner all while reducing waste.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="row paragraph">
		<div class="small-12 medium-4 columns">
			<h3 class="subheaders">Tim Hortons</h3>
			<p class="date">September 2010 - August 2012</p>
